Step 1: Calculate Gross Profit Margin.  
• Gross Profit Margin = (Gross Profit / Total Revenue) × 100  
• From the income statement, Gross Profit = 2,620,023.09 and Total Revenue = 5,760,023.09  
• Gross Profit Margin = (2,620,023.09 / 5,760,023.09) × 100 ≈ 45.42%

Step 2: Calculate Operating Cash Flow Ratio.  
• Operating Cash Flow Ratio = Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities / Total Current Liabilities  
• From the cash flow statement, Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = 803,237.11  
• From the balance sheet, Total Current Liabilities = 1,548,001.20  
• Operating Cash Flow Ratio = 803,237.11 / 1,548,001.20 ≈ 0.52

Thus, the solution in the required JSON format is:

{"solution": {'Gross Profit Margin': '45.42%', 'Operating Cash Flow Ratio': '0.52'}}
